sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Creation of an WerFault.exe in Unusual Folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects WerFault copoed to a suspicious folder, which could be a sign of WerFault DLL hijacking
DropboxAES is a simple remote access trojan (RAT) used by APT31 Group. The RAT uses the Dropbox file-sharing service for its command and control (C2) communications

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Malicious behaviour on user login (Microsoft Windows - c0d0s0 group behavior)
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects malicious registry values and unusual AppData folder modification related also to c0d0s0 group.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Files With System Process Name In Unsuspected Locations
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an executable with a system process name in folders other than the system ones (System32, SysWOW64...etc).
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Sander Wiebing, Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
